Looking at the code in `StatsUtils.kt`, I can see the `buildChange` function starting at line 219. This function constructs the change string that shows the difference and percentage when comparing stats.

The relevant part is:
```kotlin
val percentage = when (previousValue) {
    value -> "0"
    0L -> "∞"
    else -> {
        val percentageValue = difference.toFloat() / previousValue
        percentFormatter.format(value = percentageValue, rounding = HALF_UP)
    }
}
```

When `previousValue` is 0, it sets the percentage to "∞". Then at the end:
```kotlin
if (positive) {
    resourceProvider.getString(R.string.stats_traffic_increase, formattedDifference, percentage)
} else {
    resourceProvider.getString(R.string.stats_traffic_change, formattedDifference, percentage)
}
```

The issue is that when the percentage is "∞", we should not include it in the output string.

Let me look at the string resources to understand what format strings are being used.

